default1.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultIntroduction to the cycle to work scheme:default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe cycle to work scheme is a government-supported, tax-efficient and salary-sacrificed employee benefit that provides a mode through which employers can encourage their worke
defaultrs to take up cycling.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThrough the scheme, employers loan bicycles and safety equipment to their employees as a tax-exempt benefit for the purpose of commuting to and from work. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAt the end of the loan period, the employer may choose to give their employee
default the option of purchasing 
defaultthe bike and the equipment.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe scheme can save employee
defaults
default up to 42% o
defaultf
default the cost of safety equipment
default. By 
defaultdoing so, the 
defaultscheme 
defaultincentivises riders to purchase the equipment that wil
defaultl make their cycle to work safer
default. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultTo date, over 55
default0,000 individuals have taken part in the scheme, which also involves over 2,220 bike retailers 
defaultand
default over
default 
default32
default,000 employers.
default 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAlthough supportive of the scheme, Government could do more to aid its promotion
default and remove barriers to entry
default,
default 
defaulttherefore delivering g
defaultreater levels of sustainable transport and improving public health. 
default&#xa0;default2.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEncouraging cycling default&amp;default changing behaviourdefaultsdefault–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA key element of the cycle to work scheme’s effectiveness in improving
default cycling
default safety is
default through
default increasing the critical mass of cyclists on the roads. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs CTC, the national cycling charity notes
default,
default increasing cycling uptake is the surest way to improve safety. According to research, the Netherlands saw a 45% increase in cycling from 1980-2005 and a co
defaultrresponding 58% decrease in cyclist fatalities
default. Overall, 
defaultthe CTC
default suggest that doubling the amount of cyclists on the road can reduce casualties by a third. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWith this in mind, the cycle to work scheme is a proven mechanism for increasing cycling uptake, a
defaultnd therefore improving cycling safety.
default In the first half of 2013, industry data suggests 
defaultthat the scheme encouraged over 44,000 commuters to start cycling to work by bicycle.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultResearch conducted by the Cycle to Work Alliance shows that 54% of scheme users 
defaultdid not cycle to work up before they joined the initiative.
default Similarly, 72% said they would not have bought their bike and safety equipment had they not been offered through the scheme.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe financial savings that commuters make on the cost of their bike an
defaultd the safety equipment through the scheme is the fundamental aspect in their decision to sign up to the scheme. 98% of scheme users say that the
defaultse savings were either important or very important in their decision to join the scheme, and start cycling to wo
defaultrk. 
default&#xa0;default3.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFinancial savings default&amp; employer involvementdefault–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultKey to the positive impact that the cycle to work scheme has on cycling safety is the 
defaultfinancial savings that scheme users make on the cost of safety equipment.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThrough its tax efficiency, the scheme sees users
default saving up to 42% on the cost of such equipment. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSimilarly, a
defaultll members of the Cycle to Work Alliance have discussions with new users about the need for safety equipment, and the risks run if they chose not to wear such products. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultGiven the nature of the scheme as an employee benefit, it 
defaultalso 
defaultplays an important role in opening up the dialogue between employers and their staff on cycling and cycling safety. 
default&#xa0;
default4.default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultConclusions &amp; recommendationsdefault–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe cycle to work scheme is a Government-back
defaulted initiative that encourages people to commute to work by bike through making cycling and safety equipment more affordable.
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultBy doing so, the scheme increases the critical mass of cyclists on the road, which is arguably the most 
defaulteffective way to improve th
defaulte safety of cyclists. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAdditionally, the scheme increases the affordability of cycling safety equipment, and all users are encouraged to invest this in this upon their initial interactions with providers of the cycle to work scheme. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultFinally, the scheme is crucial in opening the dialogue between employers and employees on the merits of cycling, and related safety issues. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Alliance recommends that the Committee encourages Government to do more to promote the scheme, so as to improve
default cycling safety more generally. With the recent devolution of public health and sustainable transport responsibilities to local authorities, there is currently a concern that the scheme is not being adequately promoted. 
default–
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Committee should call on Government – particularly the Department for Transport – to ensure that local authorities and employers are well aware of the scheme and its benefits to both users and improving cycling safety more generally. 
